# 4Ô∏è‚É£ Why `useRef` works here (the escape hatch)

### ‚úÖ Key principle

> **Closures capture references, not mutations.**

`useRef` gives you **a stable object reference**.

***

## ‚úÖ Pattern that avoids staleness

```jsx
const countRef = useRef(count);

useEffect(() => {
  countRef.current = count;
}, [count]);

useEffect(() => {
  const id = setInterval(() => {
    console.log(countRef.current);
  }, 1000);

  return () => clearInterval(id);
}, []);
```

### ‚úÖ Why this works

*   Closure captures `countRef` (stable)
*   `.current` mutates across renders
*   Closure always reads latest value

